- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses a system for processing data streams, which is a common use case for databases. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a new execution plan optimization paradigm for data stream processing systems. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper focuses on optimizing data stream processing on modern shared-memory multicore architectures. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new approach to optimizing execution plans for data stream processing systems, which could be relevant to programming language design.
